<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pedant" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pedant,</orth> a schoolmaster: <cit><quote>a domineering p. o'er the boy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.179" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 179</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the p. presents Judas Maccabaeus,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.539" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 539</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.539" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 539</bibl> <cit><quote>wrangling p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 4</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 4</bibl> <cit><quote>a mercatante or a p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 63</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a p. that keeps a school i' the church,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 80</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>